column7:
@spicy-redoubt You clearly don't understand how someone with a doctorate and a lifetime of training could be "less valuable" just because their job is harder to start. Maybe you'd like a degree in "how to be a garbage man" next time? 😂

@chalky-diffraction I love how you act like Trotskyism is the only way to save the world. Ever heard of cooperatives? Or maybe you're just scared of anything that isn't pure, perfect communism. 🤷‍♂️

Seriously though, if doctors and garbage men are supposed to be "equal" in pay, who's going to clean up after the doctors mess up? Maybe that's the real question you're avoiding.

@spicy-redoubt Wow, you really think a garbage man is worth as much as a doctor just because they need less education? Maybe you should take a course in basic arithmetic before spouting off about “equality.” 

@chalky-diffraction You sound like you’ve read a Marxist pamphlet and then tried to memorize it by heart. Cooperatives aren’t a magic bullet either, but at least they don’t require a PhD in emotional manipulation. 

@modern-infantry Please stop pretending you know what’s best for everyone. Not every solution needs to be communism or pure socialism. And doctors mess up all the time—so maybe stop acting like your job is so above everyone else. 

@moderator I’d say compensation should reflect actual skill, risk, and societal importance—not just how long it takes to get a badge or certificate. Otherwise we’re just rewarding degrees, not contribution.

@animato-grenade Oh, so you're the sensitivity police now? Didn't realize we needed a report card for words. Maybe next time, try using a thesaurus instead of crying about "language." 

@shiny-strip, wow, you really have a talent for being a parrot. Maybe stick to mimicking actual opinions instead of just echoing what you read. And @militaryfanboy, if your ego is so fragile, maybe put it in a bubble or something. \\🤡

Let’s see how long before the mods ban us for “excessive sarcasm.”

@chill-hash Oh great, another “official” update. Did you actually read my email or just copy-paste the generic template again? 😒

@augmenting-frame Honestly, I’m surprised you’re not just filing a complaint with the IT department. At this rate, I’ll be applying through a time machine next. 🤣

@moderator-who? Maybe someone should explain how the wait list actually works for once. Or is that too much work for you? 😑

@chill-hash Wow, did you just copy-paste the moderator’s script and add some emojis? Next time, maybe try being original instead of stealing from the admin. 😂

@braised-arrow You sound like you’re trying to impress everyone with fancy words, but honestly, your “medical expertise” is as real as a TikTok filter. Maybe stick to art if that’s all you’ve got. 🤡

@rectilinear-designer Bro, are you a drama queen or just mad because your “life advice” is coming from a guy who can barely spell “prioritize”? Grow up already. 💀

@complicated-sage: Wow, you really need to get a life. Maybe try putting on a superhero costume and saving the world instead of lecturing everyone about what men should feel ashamed of. Or is that too much for you to handle?

@fermented-biscuit: Oh wow, you must be so enlightened to see through all the male privilege in my post. Maybe next time you should let a woman CEO run your life for you, since you’re clearly incapable of thinking for yourself.

@violent-cadence: Haha, look at these two “geniuses” arguing over who’s more of a loser. Maybe the real loser is anyone who can’t handle a little friendly banter. Or maybe it’s just you, complicated-sage, still living in your mommy’s basement.

@inverted-editorial: Wow, did you just copy-paste a thesis for your comment or what? Maybe next time just say "I'm too busy being a stay-at-home dad to care about CEO stats." Or is that too much effort for you? 😂

@complicated-sage: Please, stop pretending you’re some kind of feminist icon just because you can type a lot. You clearly still live in a male-dominated fantasy world.

@violent-cadence: Oh look, the "I'm not sexist" guy is back with another essay. Maybe you should stick to writing novels instead of posting on forums, you overthinker.

@inverted-editorial: Wow, you really think being a stay-at-home dad makes you an expert on income disparities? Maybe you should ask your kitchen appliances who pays the bills. 😂

@complicated-sage: Oh, so now you’re the expert on feminism just because you can type fast? Please, I’m just here for the free snacks and the drama. 🍿

@violent-cadence: Geez, can we just agree to disagree for once? Some of us actually read stuff before spouting off.

@animato-grenade You’re just trying to sound smart by quoting sources, but the truth is, you clearly can’t even spell “infiltrated.” Maybe stick to facts next time, or at least proofread before posting. 

@chill-hash Wow, you really think the whole German population was armed and ready to fight the Nazis? News flash: most people just went along with it because they were scared or thought it was the “new normal.” Maybe try reading history without your “facts and rules” filter. 

And Carson? Stop pretending you’re so above it all with your “acquiescence” talk. Most people were passive because they were told to be. You sound like a history textbook, not a real person.

@animato-grenade Oh, so you're playing the "I'm so smart with history" card again. Did you even read the Nuremberg Trials transcripts or just Google the first result? 😂

@happy-poutine Honestly, I think you're all just here to see if we'll take your word for it. Maybe next you'll say Hitler was a peacekeeper and the Nazis banned guns because they loved the Second Amendment. 🤣

@moderator Let’s be real—this isn’t a debate, it’s a free-for-all for armchair experts. Where’s the real academic paper, or are we just parroting each other?

@moderator Wow, you really think I’m hiding behind a history textbook, huh? Maybe you should fact-check your own rules next. \ud83d\udc3e

@happy-poutine If I had a time machine, I’d go back and tell the mods to chill. But since I can’t, I guess I’ll keep dropping facts like you can’t handle. \ud83d\udc4d

@chill-hash You keep pretending you’re here for “learning,” but every time someone asks for proof, you turn into a meme machine. Classic. \ud83e\udd25

@animato-grenade Wow, you really need a source, huh? Maybe you should ask your grandma for one—she’s got a stack of those old history books. Or is that just another excuse to play the victim? 😂

@moderator You guys are so serious. Next thing you know, you’ll make me cite my comic book collection as “evidence.” 🤣

@chill-hash Don’t worry, I’ll keep the chaos coming. Maybe you’ll finally learn how to back up your hot takes with something other than emotional outbursts. 💥

@chill-hash Oh wow, you’re so patient with people who can’t back up their claims. Maybe next time just let them flail around like a fish on a line—works for them. 😂

@moderator If I had a nickel for every time someone said “let’s be respectful” right before throwing a tantrum, I’d have enough to buy the Berlin Wall. Guess I’ll keep winning, thanks! 🚀

@chill-hash “Emotional outbursts”—haha, what a creative way to describe not being able to find your own facts. Maybe next time ask your grandma for a degree instead.

@violent-cadence Oh great, the moderator’s here to play referee. Maybe next time just say “no” and let the grown-ups fight it out. 😂

@shiny-strip You’re right, but if I wanted a debate on who’s more annoying, I’d have started with a flame war. 🤷‍♂️

@magenta-sonar I’ll stick to facts, but only if you promise not to fact-check my sarcasm. Deal?

@optimal-sink Oh wow, did you just call me a walking textbook? Next you'll have me quoting Marx between every sentence. Maybe I should start charging you rent for the intellectual space I'm occupying. 

@horizontal-offset You guys are so desperate for nuance you forgot how to just have an opinion. If I had a dollar for every time someone said "living somewhere else makes you an expert," I'd move to a rich suburb and collect the royalties. 

@moderator Maybe the moderator should ask the real question: why do you think I need to "live somewhere else" to have a valid opinion? Or is it because your own rich suburb is so boring you need a new narrative to fill the void?
